{
  "text": "The two systems (4.2) and (4.3) are essentially equivalent and already known in the case of scalar q n and q n (see, e.g., (4.19) or (4.21) in [CITATION_1] ). Note that ∂ t 1 and ∂ t −1 do not commute. From (4.2), we have the relation",
